<br>
Its not like it’s a huge inconvenience. Takes 160 mana to summon and takes no component cost. Is that really THAT much for a 54+ magician? Heck I’ve had magicians sitting at their bind point waiting for a rez refuse to help and  summon a focus item.<br>
<br>
I play a wizard so I’ll compare this to my class. TLs take 255 mana and most require a component. Said component is cheep but is only sold on one merchant who I happen to be kos to and since you go through so MANY it’s a nuisance to keep in stock.<br>
<br>
What it comes down to is this: I never refuse or charge for TLs, long as the person comes to me I’ll always help them out. Same thing with clarity when I’m on my enchanter. So when a magician refuses to return the favor it really makes me mad.<br>
<br>
