<br>
a) I am running between zones<br>
b) I am fighting or doing something else and I already have a focus of that type on me that I am wearing.  THEY ARE LORE.<br>
c) After a long day of being the only magician at a raid.  Summoning mod rods for everyone before each fight, then summoning mod rods non stop durring the fight, summoning focus items for everyone, then having people who came late or who werent paying attention send me a tell for focus items after I have summoned myself my own and unmemed the spells, CoHing everyone, then having to drop my group, miss most buffs and have to get them singlely, having to miss all fighting besides the actually raid mob because im cohing, and then having to CoH people who some how @#%$ up and need to be coh'd again.  I CAN ONLY TAKE SO MUCH OF THAT IN ONE DAY.  If you come to me asking for focus items after I have done that for multiple mobs, I probably will not summon you focus items.  Some days I go so crazy I dont even summon some of my own guildmates focus items on a raid after I say 50X to not send me tells for focus items until I say I am summoning them (IE after im finished with rods/cohs), and when people say right before we engage 'sorry iwasnt paying attention earlier can i have 3 focus items plz'.  Focus items are just a nice thing to have.  They will not change the outcome of a fight.<br>
