</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukrilenspiritlink.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krilen Spiritlink</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 108<br> <font color=#333333>(6/3/02 2:55:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=245.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tired of being refused Focus Items</span><hr size=1> All of these are things I recommend. They're based on my experiences.<br>
<br>
If you want focus items<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
-send tell, ask specifically for the ones you want<br>
-don't ask for more than 2. If you're a wiz, you probably want the earring, then either the ring or the bracelet depending on what you're doing. Don't ask for a mod rod along with, that's just cheesy.<br>
-Offer what you have in return when you send the tell (clarity, buff your pet, whatever)<br>
-Donate. No one has ever donated for my focus items yet, and I kinda don't appreciate that with the amount I make them for people. For a TL, I donate 75-150pp depending how much I have on me (obviously sometimes i have a measly 37pp and 12gold, so give it all)<br>
-ask a mage your level. I have no idea where my level 20 focus item spells are in my book, and which is which, so i just don't make foci for level 25-47 wizards, sorry.<br>
-come to us, don't make us go to you. duh.<br>
<br>
Oh, and don't be a prick. One time, a wiz asked me for like all 5 focus items 'to test'. I was soloing at SD, you know, the platform which sucks and you only hunt there to say you've done it once. I was always lom there because it sucked. I make the wiz all these focus, he does not donate, probably didn't even thank me, and proceeds to steal and quad kite my camp. ...<br>
<br>
<br>
Are your replies really rude? Sometimes, if i can't or don't feel like it, i say 'no.' IMO that's better than just not answering, and I'm not obligated to give a reason... am I? I suppose it could be seen as rude, but that's not how  it's intended.<br>
<br>
<br>
