<br>
The only problem I have with summoning focus items is that they're <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> LORE</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. Really, that's the only problem aside from the recast time (they really should have a 0.0 recovery time, there's no point for them to have 6.0 seconds recast).<br>
<br>
We summon a ring, bracer, and earring for ourselves, and get a tell every 10 minutes to do the same for someone else. This means we have to put our existing foci in the trade window, sit down and mem all three spells, and resummon them for ourselves, knowing that we'll have to do it again shortly. It's more of an inconvenience than anything. <p><br><center><font face="tahoma, verdana" size="1">[ <b>Baron</b> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90407" target="blank">Odibil Lauxes</a> | <b>Arch Mage</b> ]<br>Pain and Suffering tries to strike YOU, but misses!</font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utrezark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trezark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 164<br> <font color=#333333>(6/3/02 3:57:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=245.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://shadowblazer.armageddongames.com/images/Trezark/ezhmage.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tired of being refused Focus Items</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> What it comes down to is this: I never refuse or charge for TLs, long as the person comes to me I’ll always help them out. Same thing with clarity when I’m on my enchanter. So when a magician refuses to return the favor it really makes me mad.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Flip that statement around.  I never refuse or charge for focus items, long as the person comes to me I'll always help them out.  Yet I've had plenty of wizards who refuse to TL me (I keep a stack of portal fragments on me and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> always</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> offer one up front in addition to the plat, so the &quot;it takes a component&quot; argument doesn't float in this case) and chanters who refuse to give me C2.  Just the way some people are...  Likewise with Magicians, I guess.  As you can see, most of the people here would be happy to summon you a focus (mana permitting) but there are some who'd just rather not.<br>
